17 sponsor's apprentice or apprenticeship sponsor's apprentice to successfully complete an
18 apprenticeship program."
19 "(d) Upon successful completion of the requirements of a contract under this article, the
20 board shall provide a contract completion award to the employer sponsor or apprenticeship
21 sponsor. The contract completion award amount shall be determined based on the number
22 of hours of education and training required for the successful completion of the
23 apprenticeship under such apprenticeship program but shall not exceed:
24 (1) $10,000.00 per apprentice for contracts entered into before July 1, 2024; and
25 (2) $5,000.00 per apprentice for contracts entered into on or after July 1, 2024.
26 (e) Each employer sponsor or apprenticeship sponsor shall only be eligible to enter into
27 contracts under this article for up to:
28 (1) Five apprentices per year through the end of Fiscal Year 2024; and
29 (2) Ten apprentices per year beginning with the Fiscal Year 2025 and continuing each
30 fiscal year thereafter."
31 "(2) Provide funding to award employer sponsors or apprenticeship sponsors up
32 to $2,500.00 per apprentice 12 months after the start of his or her apprenticeship."
33 SECTION 2.
34 Said article is further amended in Code Section 20-4-154, relating to rules and regulations,
35 by revising paragraph (4) as follows:
36 "(4) The terms of agreement between an employer sponsor or apprenticeship sponsor and
37 the board."
38 SECTION 3.
39 This Act shall become effective upon its approval by the Governor or upon its becoming law
40 without such approval.
